<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1400,1836]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Four synonyms are listed under this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" box="[684,849,1400,1426]" pageId="14" pageNumber="19" refString="Mound, L. A. (2010) Thysanoptera (Thrips) of the World - a checklist. http: // www. ento. csiro. au / thysanoptera / worldthrips. html [accessed 11. iii. 2010]" type="journal article" year="2010">
Mound, 
<number box="[786,849,1400,1426]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and of these 
<taxonomicName box="[1021,1141,1400,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Taeniothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinani">
<emphasis box="[1021,1141,1400,1425]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">T. quinani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on a series of specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[363,529,1437,1463]" name="South Africa" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">South Africa</collectingCountry>
collected in the flowers of a vine. The Gladiolus 
<taxonomicName box="[1176,1260,1437,1463]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Thrips</taxonomicName>
is now found worldwide, but presumably originated in southern Africa in association with the extensive 
<taxonomicName box="[1231,1339,1474,1500]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Iridaceae</taxonomicName>
flora of that area.
</paragraph>
